\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 78. D. cintranus }Boiss. & Reuter,{\i  Pugillus }20 (1852). Glabrous perennial 10-50 cm, with trailing, woody stems. Leaves 0·5-2(-5) mm wide, flat, acute or acuminate, the lower sometimes obtuse. Inflorescence simple or branched. Epicalyx-scales 4-6, 1/3 - 1/2 as long as calyx, ovate, cuspidate to acuminate. Calyx 17-28 × 4·5-6 mm, not purple-tinged. Petal-limb 4-12 mm, obovate, dentate, scarcely bearded to glabrous.{\i  Spain and Portugal}. Hs Lu.
